Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Colliders
    Implements and sets the position of our collision objects.
    CollisionAlgorithm
    This class calculates and implements the specific algorithm necessary when the frog collides with any moving object in the game
    Destination
    This class represents the lily pods at the end of each level to which each frog must reach to complete a level It extends the DynamicObject class as the lily pads are also these types of objects
    DestinationInfo
    Represents the class that stores information for the final pads that the frog must reach to complete the level.
    DynamicObject
    An abstract class to be used for all objects that aren't static, such as our frog, obstacles, and even the weather.
    DynamicObjectGenerator
    This class generates the Dynamic Object that is then used to visually represent the object in the game.
    Frogger
    This class represents the actual frog object that the user controls using the keyboard
    GUI
    This class creates the GUI that the user sees and ultimately plays the game in.
    JUFroggerTest
    Extensive JUnit Testing of all testable (non-GUI involved) classes in our program.
    ObstacleFive
    Represents one of the obstacles that the frog must encounter.
    ObstacleFour
    Creates an obstacle that the frog must encounter as it completes each level.
    ObstacleOne
    Represents an obstacle that the frog encounters in the game.
    ObstacleThree
    Creates an obstacle that the frog must encounter on its way across the world.
    ObstacleTwo
    Creates an obstacle that the frog encounters during the game.
    Pad
    This class creates the pad on which the frog goes to cross the river The class only has a constructor that allows for the initialization of the pad.
    SecondaryPad
    Creates a shorter pad for the frog to travel on and cross the river.
    Weather
    Creates a weather condition for the frog to struggle with during the game.
    WeatherBuild
    Weather generator class which allows for the graphic representation of the Weather (lightning)
    World
    This class is the main class of the Frogger game that has to be run in order for the game to be launched.
